x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Selzer, of course, =
is widely respected among her peers. She=E2=80=99s spent three decades in t=
he polling business and boasts an A+ rating from <b>Nate Silver</b>, who ha=
s described her status among pollsters as =E2=80=9Cnear-oracular.=E2=80=9D =
Indeed, Selzer=E2=80=99s sterling reputation was the main reason that many =
in Washington and the media took her startling Iowa result at least somewha=
t seriously. (Trump, of course, had won the state by eight points four year=
s prior.) Even among the veteran political operators who wrote off the Harr=
is +3 number as an outlier, the prospect that pollsters nationwide might be=
 significantly undercounting Democratic votes fomented a temporary media na=
rrative that Kamala=E2=80=99s campaign had crucial momentum heading into th=
e final days of the race. <br/><br/>Two weeks after the election, Selzer an=
nounced that she would be retiring from the
polling business to explore =E2=80=9Cother ventures and opportunities=E2=80=
=9D=E2=80=94a decision she said she made last year. =E2=80=9CWould I have l=
iked to make this announcement after a final poll aligned with Election Day=
 results? Of course,=E2=80=9D she wrote in a guest essay for <i>The</i> <i>=
Des Moines Register</i>. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s ironic that it=E2=80=99s jus=
t the opposite.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>But Trump was still fuming over the last-=
minute narrative shift that the poll generated. He was also emboldened by A=
BC News=E2=80=99s capitulation in his defamation lawsuit against the networ=
k and <b>George Stephanopoulos</b>, who said on air that Trump had been fou=
nd liable for the =E2=80=9Crape=E2=80=9D rather than =E2=80=9Csexual assaul=
t=E2=80=9D of writer <b>E. Jean Carroll</b>. The president-elect now appear=
s eager to run up the score. <br/><br/>Ahead of filing the lawsuit Monday e=
vening, Trump previewed his plans in an afternoon press conference. =E2=80=
=9CWe have to straighten out our press,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9COur pres=
s is very corrupt, almost as corrupt as
our elections.=E2=80=9D Besides the now-resolved ABC News suit, Trump is al=
so suing CBS News for <i>$10 billion</i> for the way it edited <b>Bill Whit=
aker</b>=E2=80=99s <i>60 Minutes</i> interview with Harris=E2=80=94claiming=
 the edited broadcast amounted to =E2=80=9Cpartisan and unlawful acts of el=
ection and voter interference=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94and he=E2=80=99s <u><a href=
=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0d=
